#Implications of Human Uploading

<p><i>Note: I am not an expert in this area. You would probably do better to
ask a science fiction author, Robin Hanson, or yourself.</i></p>

<p>The practical availability of reliable human uploading may have some of the following implications:<ul>

<li><b>Most people would be uploads</b>. Uploads would take up very little
physical space and rather little energy compared to
cell-based<footnote>*<span>Read <i>carbon-based</i> if you prefer, but there's
a good chance future computers will be based on carbon too.</span></footnote>
humans, and they would be cheap to copy.</li>

